                        Emeril's Coastal \n                         \n                                                             \n                 \n                               \n                   \n                     Las Vegas \n                                                                                       \n                           Emeril's New Orleans Fish House \n                         \n                                               \n                           Delmonico Steakhouse \n                         \n                                                             \n                 \n                           \n           \n             About Emeril \n           \n             Gift Cards \n           \n             Press \n           \n             Careers \n           icon--reservations New Orleans \n                 \n                  Meril                 \n               \n                 \n                  Emeril's                 \n               Miramar Beach \n                 \n                  Emeril's Coastal                 \n               Las Vegas \n                 \n                  Delmonico Steakhouse                 \n               \n                 \n                  Emeril's New Orleans Fish House                 \n               Chef E.J. Lagasse Shares the Advice his\u00a0Dad Gave Him \u201cI\u2019m still developing my own style, but at Emeril\u2019s [Restaurant] I\u2019m working hard to meld those big flavors from my father\u2019s food that everyone loves with more luxurious technique and presentation,\u201d says E.J. \u201cI want to pay homage to the way my father transformed American cooking while pushing the envelope gastronomically, too.\u201d Meet E.J. Lagasse, the Nineteen-Year-Old New\u00a0Chef at World-Famous Emeril\u2019s \nBy the time E.J. Lagasse was born, his father,  Emeril Lagasse , had been a celebrity chef for more than a decade. But little E.J., quite logically, assumed dad\u2019s fame sprang from providing the voice for a cartoon alligator in the 2009 Disney movie  The Princess and the Frog.  \u201cThat\u2019s why I thought he was always getting his picture taken,\u201d he says. Chef EJ Lagasse on How His Father Inspired\u00a0His Career \nAward-winning chef Emeril Lagasse became a national figure as a host of several popular cooking shows. But in New Orleans, he\u2019s known for his flagship restaurant \u201cEmeril\u2019s.\u201d It\u2019s been an institution in the city for more than 30 years. His restaurant has undergone some big changes thanks to the new young chef at its helm \u2014 E.J. Lagasse. Best Restaurant Wine Lists in New Orleans \nWinner of Wine Spectator\u2019s \u201cGrand Award\u201d for 20 consecutive years, Emeril\u2019s\u00a0boasts a fabulous cellar of nearly 2,650 selections and 16,000 bottles collected by sommelier Johnny Slamon. In the Salon, guests can experience a rotating list of specially curated wines by the glass. Celebrate in grand style with private dining for 12 in the restaurant\u2019s wine cellar, with its wine cask ceiling and walls of spectacular wine. Chef Emeril Lagasse is Finally Ready to Kick it Down a Notch \nHe was the most famous chef in the world. And then, after being spurned by the network he helped create, he wasn\u2019t. But the King of Bam! is done being angry and ready to get philosophical. Ian McNulty: Emeril\u2019s goes even more upscale. See what it\u2019s like to dine here now \nAlways high-end, and boundary-pushing in its first heyday for its namesake chef\u2019s \u201cnew New Orleans cooking,\u201d Emeril\u2019s today feels like\u00a0a new restaurant in some ways. At Emeril\u2019s Restaurant, a father\u2019s legacy, a son\u2019s ambition, a New Orleans icon\u2019s next act \nFrom a table at Emeril\u2019s Restaurant, diners can catch glimpses of the cavernous, gleaming kitchen at work. It\u2019s a choreography of cooks in formal whites moving between steel tables, roaring stoves and racks of hanging pots as plates make their way through a progression of specialized stations. Bam! Emeril Lagasse on Kicking Your Content Up A Notch \nFrom restaurants to media, Emeril Lagasse has had a remarkable career. Through it all the famed chef and humanitarian has been able to grow his business empire by prioritizing people. Listen to learn about making memorable moments with hospitality, putting relationships first, and creating content with purpose. Emeril Cooks Celebrates NOLA Dining \nWorld-renowned Chef and Restauranteur Emeril Lagasse discusses his new Roku show Emeril Cooks. The World\u2019s Best Restaurant Selection: Emeril\u2019s New Orleans \nThe 2023 awards recognize chefs, restaurants, and regions who are making waves in the industry through excellent cooking, innovation, sustainability, authenticity, and more. Where to Drink Wine in Las Vegas Right Now \nTry one of these 18 restaurants and wine lounges to get your wine fix in Las Vegas. Pour Over What New Orleans Wine & Food Experience Has In Store This Year \nYou can find a list of the participating wineries\u00a0 here , and below you can whet your appetite with a glowing list of the highly-rated restaurants that\u2019ll be at various NOWFE events.\u00a0(ENO) Emeril Lagasse\u2019s New Orleans must-dos \nCall him \u201cMr. Bam,\u201d the \u201cElvis of TV chefs\u201d or simply Emeril, this forerunner of \u201cNew New Orleans\u201d cuisine has a name that precedes him. Four chefs, one extraordinary city \nFour chefs \u2014 Leah Chase, Emeril Lagasse, Donald Link and Nina Compton \u2014 sat down for an intimate CNN family meal to talk about their unique journeys, both to restaurant kitchens and to the extraordinary city of New Orleans. 9 Chefs Share Their Go-To Dinners They Cook For Their Kids \nBolognese, stir-fry, and linguine with clams \u2014 Emeril Lagasse, chef and TV personality Gravity-defying dessert, $195 mac\u2019n\u2019cheese and Beyonc\u00e9\u2019s guacamole: the tastiest food TV \nEat the World With Emeril Lagasse Amazon Star Chef Challenge: Pairing with Emeril Lagasse and Jos\u00e9 Andr\u00e9s \nChef Jos\u00e9 Andr\u00e9s and Wine Spectator\u2019s Thomas Matthews battle to select the best wine for chef Emeril Lagasse\u2019s twist on a Reuben. Where to eat in New Orleans, according to Emeril Lagasse \nChef Emeril Lagasse is known worldwide for his innovative dishes, award-winning restaurants and overall exuberance. What Ella Brennan Meant to Me \n\u201cShe was the grande dame of our business, not just in New Orleans but America.\u201d Chefs Pay Tribute to NOLA Restaurant Legend Ella Brennan \nEmeril Lagasse \u00a9 2023 Emeril's Homebase. All Rights Reserved. \u00a9 2023 Emeril's Homebase. All Rights Reserved.", "size": 49938, "depth": 1, "download_timeout": 180.0, "download_slot": "emerilsrestaurants.com", "download_latency": 0.15006065368652344, "redirect_times": 1, "redirect_ttl": 19, "redirect_urls": "https://emerilsrestaurants.com/press", "redirect_reasons": "301", "status": 200, "links_url": "https://emerilsrestaurants.com@@https://emerilsrestaurants.com/emerils-new-orleans@@https://www.exploretock.com/emerils-restaurant-new-orleans@@https://emerilsrestaurants.com/meril@@https://www.opentable.com/r/meril-reservations-new-orleans?restref=269761@@https://emerilsrestaurants.com/emerils-coastal@@https://www.opentable.com/r/emerils-coastal-reservations-miramar-beach?restref=444583&lang=en-US&ot_source=Restaurant%20website@@https://emerilsrestaurants.com/emerils-new-orleans-fish-house@@https://www.opentable.com/emerils-new-orleans-fish-house-reservations-las-vegas?restref=1822@@https://emerilsrestaurants.com/delmonico-steakhouse@@https://www.opentable.com/delmonico-steakhouse-reservations-las-vegas?restref=1823@@https://emerilsrestaurants.com/about-emeril/@@https://emerilsrestaurants.com/gift-cards/@@https://emerilsrestaurants.com/press@@https://emerilsrestaurants.com/employment/@@https://emerilsrestaurants.com/press/@@https://emerilsrestaurants.com/emer